Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a pale buff-coloured pottery vessel, the fabric is greyish in section, the exterior is covered with a cream-coloured slip and very faint traces of five lines of black-painted hieratic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393987) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393987)
